{
  "stem": "14897.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father spent a year working for an organization called [NON-ENGLISH], which is I guess like Blue Cross Blue Shield in the United States, and learning about subtropical diseases and so on.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after a year, we used the $8,000 that had been in the United States waiting for us-- my uncle, having charge of it, who sent it to us-- sent it to us, to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we got an apartment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father organized a laboratory.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was-- I had studied for a year, took the exams, and then takes months to get the results.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because these exams, called London Matriculation, kind of like equivalency exams in United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You take them, then they go to England to the University of London, and it takes months before you get the results.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at the same time, I was already applying to universities in United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the second year, I was working with my father, as his assistant, and hoping to get into a university in United States, and I did.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just briefly--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I know how it got to [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Vilna, ?] through people who would carry the money.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think my uncle brought it out when he came.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This is the uncle who lived in New York City-- brought it out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he kept it for us, you know, and made it available when we needed it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's OK, that's OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got accepted to two universities, NYU and Columbia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I looked at the map of Manhattan.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My uncle lived on 87th Street and West End Avenue, which was closer to Columbia, so I went Columbia, never knowing that it was the better of the two schools.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
